<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=732&amp;p=3627#p3627"><![CDATA[
classic shell has been around longer than windows 8, and thus wasn't designed specifically for it, those pictures are from windows 8, there not transformations of windows 8 caused by classic shell.<br /><br /><br />box shaped plain window is caused by windows 8 theme... <br />lack of transparency is also part of windows 8... neither of these things is changed by classic shell<br /><br />If you would like transparency/blur back for your windows: <br /><a href="http://www.msfn.org/board/topic/161788-aero-glass-for-win8-rc2/" class="postlink">http://www.msfn.org/board/topic/161788-aero-glass-for-win8-rc2/</a><br /><br />If you want a theme similar to windows 7 (although the corners are still 'boxy')<br /><a href="http://xxinightxx.deviantart.com/art/Aero-8-350491112?offset=0#comments" class="postlink">http://xxinightxx.deviantart.com/art/Aero-8-350491112?offset=0#comments</a><br /><br /><br />In-line submenus is a much requested feature, and your request have been taken into account for possible development plans...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Sat Jun 08, 2013 5:20 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
